tags.name: Saint Nicholas Avenue & 168th Street at Southeast Corner

tags.description: No photo, but this gate likely looks and works identically to the one on the other end of this pedestrianized street.
view of the former location of the Polo Grounds
Two gates one after the other.  Never tried going through them.  Have never seen them open.  Don't know if they can open.  There's a dirt desire line just outside them where you can bike past.
On 2024-03-10 this footpath was muddy though in some places there were wood chips over the mud.
